OL,7,FThat's still quite the "hole". And,
OL,8,Fnote: this hole is entirely separate
OL,9,Fto the hole in the public finances of
OL,10,Fgetting on for #40 billion a year that
OL,11,Fthe Institute for Fiscal Studies (IFS)
OL,12,Fidentified back in March and
OL,13,Fhighlighted repeatedly during the
OL,14,Felection campaign.
OL,16,FThe implied spending squeeze on local
OL,17,Fgovernment services, courts, prisons
OL,18,Fand public investment in this
OL,19,Fparliament has yet to be addressed.
